  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I came in at night to my aunt's house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that was my first experience with the Germans, the first day when I came to Zlotchov.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't have any-- during the time when I was in Zlotchov, I don't know what happened there, because there was no communication, you know?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well-- well, what I want to say is when I was in Zlotchov under the Germans, I didn't have any contact with my family.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had only one postcard from my mother after six months when we were in Zlotchov, and the Germans were there, that everything is fine, they're alive, and everything is all right.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For me, it was no way I-- I could get to them, because it was prohibited for Jews to do any travel.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was just impossible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Wherever you are, you had to stay there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were just hoping for the best.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
